summary: Space node for / at /

name: entity
summary: Space node for entity at /entity

name: 0:move 1
summary: Move forward

name: 1:move -1
summary: Move backward

name: 2:turn 1
summary: yaw degrees add 90, when yaw degree is 0, next turn 1 will be 90

name: 3:turn -1
summary: yaw degrees minus 90, when yaw degree is 0, next turn -1 will be 270

name: 4:look 1
summary: Look down, view degree minus 90, max is -180

name: 5:look -1
summary: Look up, view degree add 90, min is 180, when view degree is 180, next look 1 will not change

name: 6:jumpmove
summary: Jump while moving forward, when there is an obstacle in front, can jump over the obstacle

name: 7:attack
summary: Attack the target in front 1-2 blocks, collect items. When you need to collect items at REL y=0, first use look 1 to adjust the view to level 0, then attack, when collecting REL y=1 items, no need to adjust the view, when collecting REL y=2 items, need to use look -1 to adjust the view to level 2

name: 8:use
summary: Use item, use the currently selected hotbar item on the target in front 1-2 blocks, must have a target to use the item

name: 9:jumpuse
summary: Jump and use item

name: 10:discardcurrentitem
summary: Discard the currently selected item

name: 11:hotbar.[int]
summary: Select hotbar slot [int]

name: 12:swapinventoryitems [i j]
summary: Swap inventory slots i and j items

name: 13:combineinventoryitems [i j]
summary: Combine inventory slots i and j items

name: 14:craft [item_name]
summary: Craft [item_name] when enough materials in inventory

name: 15:nearbycraft [item_name]
summary: Need to place a crafting table in the surrounding environment first, then craft [item_name] using nearby crafting table when enough materials in inventory

name: 16:nearbysmelt [item_name]
summary: Smelt [item_name] using nearby furnace when enough materials in inventory
